## 🚀 Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/F1SMV/Neural-DX-Watcher.git
cd Neural-DX-Watcher
chmod +x start.sh
./start.sh
```

Available at `http://localhost:8000`

> 💡 A **Raspberry Pi** is recommended for its low power consumption, but the program runs on any Linux PC.

---

## ⚙️ Technical Architecture

- Backend: Python / Flask
- Frontend: HTML / CSS / JavaScript
- Cluster: Telnet DX Cluster
- Analysis: dedicated Python scripts
- Storage: memory + local JSON + **SQLite**

No cloud dependency.

---

## 🗂️ Version History

### v10.3 — 2m Surge Detection · AI Insight Navigation · Fixes

#### 📡 2m Surge Detection

- 2m was **excluded** from surge detection (to avoid false positives)
- Now included with **double threshold**: rate × 2.0 and minimum 8 recent spots
- Real Es openings on 2m trigger the alert · normal local activity does not

#### 🔗 Navigation Fixed

- All "AI Insight" links still pointed to `/analysis` → corrected to `/ai-insight`
- `map-v11.html` removed (obsolete test page, integrated into cockpit)

---

### v10.2 — TLE JSON OMM Migration · Favicon · AI Insight · Fixes

#### 🛰️ TLE JSON OMM Migration (CelesTrak)

CelesTrak will exhaust 5-digit catalog numbers (~69999) around **July 12, 2026**. Preventive migration to JSON OMM format.

**New TLE loading architecture — 3 layers:**

1. **JSON OMM sources (priority)** — CelesTrak GP API:
   - `gp.php?GROUP=amateur&FORMAT=json` → all amateur satellites
   - `gp.php?GROUP=stations&FORMAT=json` → ISS, CSS Tiangong, etc.
   - `NORAD_CAT_ID` native integer (unlimited), `TLE_LINE1`/`TLE_LINE2` compatible with sgp4 unchanged
2. **Text fallback (AMSAT nasa.all)** — supplements JSON for missing satellites
3. **Consolidated log** — satellites loaded per source at startup

#### ⚡ Favicon

- ⚡ cyan lightning bolt on dark background, inline base64 SVG in all templates
- No extra file required

#### 🧠 Page Renamed: Analysis → AI Insight

- Template renamed `ai_insight.html`, route `/ai-insight`
- Backward compatibility: `/analysis` and `/analysis.html` redirect automatically

#### 🎨 AI Insight Page Improvements

- Missing CSS variables fixed (`--font-sans`, `--font-display`, `--success`)
- Long Distance enriched: distance (km), band, mode, time
- Rare calls **clickable** → quick add to watchlist
- META analysis error: `confirm()` replaced by inline HTML dialog, contextual error message (no more popup window)
- Last update indicator + refresh spinner
- Global FR/EN language toggle persisted in localStorage
- Chart.js improvements: custom tooltips, `easeOutQuart` animation, subtle grid

#### 🔧 Various Fixes

- **World** navigation: AI Insight link added, brand name corrected
- Version number updated to V10.2 everywhere

---

### v10.1 — COCKPIT Redesign · Radar Sweep · Improved Satellites · Bug Fixes

#### 🎛 COCKPIT Mode Visual Overhaul

**VHF PROPAGATION · VOACAP** — HTML table 4 bands (50/70/144/432 MHz) × 6 time slots, color-coded cells

**Radar Sweep Effect** (🆕 ON/OFF toggle)
- Canvas beam via `requestAnimationFrame`, centered on operator's QTH
- Concentric rings, fading trail, glowing QTH dot · State saved in localStorage

**Unified Activity Scale Legend** (🆕) — 6 levels: CLOSED → HOT

**Cockpit Watchlist Tracking** (🆕) — column 3, direct display sorted by last spot

**DX Spot Feed** — orange calls, yellow watchlist, red new DXCC, distance first

**Page scrolling** — wheel freely scrolls the cockpit page

**Opening Strength gauge** — 132px → 200px

#### 🛰️ Satellites Page

- Uplink/downlink frequencies from SatNOGS (6h cache, parallel preload on startup)
- Satellite type auto-inferred (amateur/weather/station)
- **Azimuth fix** 🔴: `atan2(-e, s)` → `atan2(e, -s)` — 180° offset corrected

---

### v10.0 — Predictive Engine · Sparklines · Push Alerts (optional)

**Predictive engine** (`predictor.py`): SQLite collection, seasonal Es scoring, TOP 5 predictions 24h  
**Sparklines** DX Feed: 40×14px canvas, 6 × 10-min bars  
**Push alerts** (`ntfy.sh`): watchlist / NEW DXCC / 6m opening, 15-min SQLite cooldown  
**Design**: glassmorphism, CRT scanlines, cyan palette

